1
00:00:21,290 --> 00:00:25,187
這才是去海邊的樣子
MacGYVER: Now, this is what goin' to the beach is all about.

2
00:00:27,127 --> 00:00:30,824
( women shouting )

3
00:00:33,070 --> 00:00:36,691
外面有幾個美女
Boy, there's some fine-lookin' women out there, huh?

4
00:00:36,810 --> 00:00:38,980
-你有望遠鏡嗎？ -有, 在廚房
You got those binoculars?

5
00:00:38,304 --> 00:00:39,999
Yeah, in the kitchen.

6
00:00:45,016 --> 00:00:46,303
話說回來
MacGYVER: On the other hand,

7
00:00:46,317 --> 00:00:49,988
我從不覺得拯救女將軍 是海灘樂趣

8
00:00:46,413 --> 00:00:47,380
rescuin' a lady general

9
00:00:47,480 --> 00:00:50,677
has never been my idea of beach fun.

10
00:01:09,502 --> 00:01:11,197
( doorknob rattles )

11
00:01:30,728 --> 00:01:31,796
好了

12
00:01:30,957 --> 00:01:34,586
看看有什麼可用的
All right, let's see what we've got to work with.

13
00:01:43,040 --> 00:01:45,703
這是好的開始
Okay, this seems to be a good start.

14
00:01:54,652 --> 00:01:58,076
我只需要他們分心幾秒鐘
All I need is a few seconds of distraction.

15
00:02:21,950 --> 00:02:24,410
老天, 你看看
Oh, man,

16
00:02:23,643 --> 00:02:25,440
look at that!

17
00:02:48,330 --> 00:02:49,536
（蔬菜油）

18
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:43,013
我一定要出去看看
Oh, I gotta go outside and check this out.

19
00:03:55,468 --> 00:03:55,934
What the...?

20
00:03:55,870 --> 00:03:57,037
我們走, 快點
Hey, let's go! Come on!

21
00:03:57,100 --> 00:03:57,604
誰在裡面？

22
00:03:57,103 --> 00:03:58,229
Who's in there?

23
00:03:59,439 --> 00:04:00,064
Hey!

24
00:04:00,173 --> 00:04:02,300
( grunting )

25
00:04:03,680 --> 00:04:05,507
看來妳對他們 什麼都沒說吧, 將軍
I'll bet you didn't tell them a thing, huh, General?

26
00:04:05,450 --> 00:04:06,772
我把妳弄出去吧
Let's get you outta here.

27
00:04:08,250 --> 00:04:10,279
手銬, 可惡
Handcuffs! Damn!

28
00:04:15,188 --> 00:04:16,621
( men grunting and shouting )

29
00:04:19,692 --> 00:04:21,557
( grunting )

30
00:04:32,711 --> 00:04:33,778
抓住他

31
00:04:37,544 --> 00:04:38,769
她不見了
She's gone!

32
00:04:38,878 --> 00:04:40,345
( both yell )

33
00:04:41,014 --> 00:04:42,879
( grunting and gasping )

34
00:04:49,394 --> 00:04:50,428
別動

35
00:04:49,689 --> 00:04:51,900
坐下, 別動
Stay! Sit! Stay!

36
00:04:53,665 --> 00:04:55,054
好狗狗
Good dogs.

37
00:05:05,740 --> 00:05:08,706
派克曼, 我是馬蓋先
Yeah, Packman? MacGyver.

38
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:10,673
你失蹤的女將軍
You know that lady general you lost?

39
00:05:11,549 --> 00:05:13,373
我找到她了
Well, I found her.

40
00:05:37,700 --> 00:05:41,708
馬蓋先 第一季

41
00:06:29,560 --> 00:06:31,790
目標馬蓋先

42
00:06:31,929 --> 00:06:34,718
我真的得重新思考我的人生了
MacGYVER: I really have to rethink my life.

43
00:06:35,533 --> 00:06:38,026
才把女將軍送回五角大廈
I hardly get the lady general back to the Pentagon

44
00:06:38,102 --> 00:06:40,895
就接到紅色警戒的任務
when I get a Code Red priority.

45
00:06:45,509 --> 00:06:49,801
所以我在這個月光照耀的夜晚
So, here I am on a moonlit night starin' down the throat

46
00:06:48,446 --> 00:06:52,878
盯著這座全新的 中東核能精煉廠
of a brand-new Middle Eastern nuclear refining plant

47
00:06:52,750 --> 00:06:54,674
它存在的原因不外乎
put on this good Earth for no other reason

48
00:06:54,580 --> 00:06:58,020
就是要讓某個軍事狂人 炸掉他的鄰居
than to allow some crazy strong man

49
00:06:56,883 --> 00:06:58,680
to blow up his neighbors.

50
00:07:05,229 --> 00:07:07,949
猜猜華府要我做什麼
Guess what Washington asked me to do.

51
00:07:59,180 --> 00:08:00,770
好, 準備好要炸了
All right, ready to blow it.

52
00:08:00,720 --> 00:08:02,905
4點30分來接我
Be at the pickup zone at 0430.

53
00:08:43,594 --> 00:08:44,851
好了
All right.

54
00:08:57,340 --> 00:09:00,438
回到家了, 夠了就是夠了
Home-- enough is enough.

55
00:09:00,411 --> 00:09:04,448
我不會在任何條件下 為任何原因
I will not, under any circumstances

56
00:09:02,975 --> 00:09:05,910
for any reason whatsoever answer the phone...

57
00:09:04,449 --> 00:09:05,750
再接電話了

58
00:09:06,250 --> 00:09:08,846
可能吧
probably... again.

59
00:09:11,020 --> 00:09:14,313
沒錯, 我的確回到家了
Yes, I am definitely home.

60
00:10:12,150 --> 00:10:12,902
什麼事？
Well?

61
00:10:12,750 --> 00:10:15,708
我只是來恭喜你
I just dropped in to congratulate you.

62
00:10:15,590 --> 00:10:17,112
非常謝謝你
Thank you very much.

63
00:10:17,722 --> 00:10:20,511
部裡很感激
The Department is grateful.

64
00:10:21,125 --> 00:10:22,812
不客氣
You're welcome.

65
00:10:22,927 --> 00:10:24,713
我很累了
And I'm very tired.

66
00:10:24,660 --> 00:10:26,585
我不是來派任務給你的
I'm not offering you an assignment.

67
00:10:26,597 --> 00:10:28,125
我是來警告你
I'm giving you a warning.

68
00:10:28,099 --> 00:10:29,429
你成了目標了
You're a target.

69
00:10:29,734 --> 00:10:31,820
那你就要說清楚了
Now, that I'd like spelled out.

70
00:10:31,769 --> 00:10:33,438
你把核能廠處理掉的時候

71
00:10:31,931 --> 00:10:35,196
When you put away that nuclear installation, they ID'd you.

72
00:10:33,638 --> 00:10:35,069
他們認出你了

73
00:10:35,070 --> 00:10:37,163
第二天就放話出去
The contract went out the next day.

74
00:10:37,269 --> 00:10:38,964
他們僱用了阿克斯特
They hired Axminster.

75
00:10:40,010 --> 00:10:42,300
他殺了謝赫哈三, 對吧？
He took out Sheikh Hussein, didn't he?

76
00:10:42,250 --> 00:10:44,035
就在禱告時
Right in the middle of prayers.

77
00:10:44,080 --> 00:10:46,007
把他炸得當場上西天
Blew him straight to Allah

78
00:10:46,317 --> 00:10:48,643
還順道殺了37個人
and killed 37 others along the way.

79
00:10:48,520 --> 00:10:51,842
我們監看這裡的同時 你應該出城去
You oughta get out of town while we, uh, stake this place out.

80
00:10:52,520 --> 00:10:54,780
巴尼, 我的麻煩 我喜歡自己處理
Barney, I like to take care of my own messes.

81
00:10:54,650 --> 00:10:55,717
馬蓋先
MacGyver,

82
00:10:55,620 --> 00:10:59,052
阿克斯特可以為了你 燒光整個街區
Axminster would torch the whole block just to get you.

83
00:10:59,730 --> 00:11:02,866
我可以幫你 弄個安全無虞的住處
Now, I can set up a safe house, full security,

84
00:11:02,867 --> 00:11:04,568
除非你自己有地方
unless, uh, you've got someplace

85
00:11:04,530 --> 00:11:07,226
可以待上幾個星期
you'd like to settle in for a couple of weeks.

86
00:11:08,570 --> 00:11:10,863
其實, 是有趟旅行
You know, there is a kind of a,

87
00:11:11,840 --> 00:11:14,029
我想了一陣子了
a trip I've been toying with.

88
00:11:13,740 --> 00:11:15,539
現在就去吧
Take it now.

89
00:11:15,510 --> 00:11:18,337
只要是能讓你消失的
As long as it spells one word: "lost."

90
00:11:18,477 --> 00:11:19,876
( sighs )

91
00:11:20,180 --> 00:11:22,142
我想我的確該拜訪一個人
I guess I do owe a visit.

92
00:11:22,086 --> 00:11:23,510
是誰？
To who?

93
00:11:25,023 --> 00:11:26,742
這是私事
It's personal, Barney.

94
00:11:27,490 --> 00:11:30,750
好吧, 只要告訴我地點
Okay, just tell me if and where.

95
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:32,954
我會處理, 上校
I'll handle that, Colonel,

96
00:11:33,060 --> 00:11:35,259
你不需要知道
and you don't need to know where.

97
00:11:36,130 --> 00:11:38,093
你只要把阿克斯特處理好
You just take care of Axminster.

98
00:11:50,180 --> 00:11:51,900
你看看這個
Take a look at this!

99
00:11:52,984 --> 00:11:54,237
什麼？
What?

100
00:11:54,218 --> 00:11:58,384
有個女人被外星人攻擊 還生了外星人寶寶
It says this here lady was attacked by aliens

101
00:11:56,649 --> 00:11:58,844
and had an alien baby.

102
00:11:59,260 --> 00:12:00,409
真的嗎？
No kiddin'?

103
00:12:00,350 --> 00:12:02,922
對, 在阿拉巴馬州
Yeah. In Alabama somewhere.

104
00:12:04,028 --> 00:12:06,354
在那裡外星人是大事
Big on aliens in Alabama.

105
00:12:06,930 --> 00:12:08,900
沒錯, 一堆怪人
No lie.

106
00:12:08,160 --> 00:12:09,684
Full of strange people.

107
00:12:09,734 --> 00:12:11,429
所以我才往北走
That's why I'm goin' North,

108
00:12:11,502 --> 00:12:13,859
回去看看家人
back to see my family for a while.

109
00:12:15,773 --> 00:12:16,924
有道理
Makes sense.

110
00:12:19,980 --> 00:12:23,180
我十歲起就沒見過我外公了
MacGYVER: I hadn't seen my grandfather since I was ten.

111
00:12:23,181 --> 00:12:25,537
他是我僅有的家人
He was all the family I had left,

112
00:12:26,020 --> 00:12:27,705
而我們形同陌路
and we were strangers.

113
00:12:30,649 --> 00:12:37,851
( phone ringing )

114
00:12:37,829 --> 00:12:39,788
我是馬蓋先
MacGYVER: Hi. MacGyver here.

115
00:12:39,730 --> 00:12:42,292
聽到嗶聲後 告訴我你在想什麼
When you hear the beep, let me know what's on your mind.

116
00:12:42,394 --> 00:12:43,383
( beep )

117
00:12:43,330 --> 00:12:45,726
我告訴你我在想什麼, 孩子
JACKSON: I'll let you know what's on my mind, bud.

118
00:12:45,770 --> 00:12:48,770
把電話拿起來 我不喜歡跟機器說話

119
00:12:45,865 --> 00:12:47,264
Pick up that phone and talk to me.

120
00:12:47,366 --> 00:12:49,334
I got no mind for machines.

121
00:12:49,670 --> 00:12:52,236
真是, 你大概不在家
Oh, damn, I guess you aren't there!

122
00:12:52,510 --> 00:12:53,810
我是你的…
This is your...

123
00:12:54,110 --> 00:12:55,650
我是哈利.傑克森
This is Harry Jackson.

124
00:12:55,141 --> 00:12:56,972
The-the clerk from the general store

125
00:12:55,747 --> 00:12:59,340
雜貨店的店員給我這個號碼
brung me up a note with this phone number.

126
00:12:59,183 --> 00:13:01,037
他說你要來看我
He says you're comin' to visit me.

127
00:13:01,190 --> 00:13:02,345
阿克斯特
Axminster!

128
00:13:02,110 --> 00:13:04,439
我只是想告訴你…
JACKSON: And I just want to say...

129
00:13:05,260 --> 00:13:06,790
別過來, 我很忙

130
00:13:05,317 --> 00:13:05,908
don't come.

131
00:13:06,018 --> 00:13:07,383
I'm busy.

132
00:13:08,259 --> 00:13:10,728
你大概已經在路上了
Ah, hell, you're probably on the way here already.

133
00:13:11,929 --> 00:13:13,616
如果你又打去雜貨店
You can phone the general store again.

134
00:13:13,630 --> 00:13:17,594
電話是303-555-7702
It's area code 303, triple-five, double-seven-oh-two.

135
00:13:17,735 --> 00:13:19,558
我立刻去查
I'll try and run that down right away.

136
00:13:43,861 --> 00:13:45,797
真是個美麗的地方
MacGYVER: What a beautiful part of the world.

137
00:13:46,460 --> 00:13:48,370
什麼都有, 就是沒有人
Has everything but people.

138
00:13:49,870 --> 00:13:52,227
我不明白我外公是怎麼了
I got to wonder what happened to my grandfather

139
00:13:51,970 --> 00:13:55,027
為什麼決定這樣離群索居
that made him decide to live in such isolation.

140
00:13:56,970 --> 00:13:59,772
事實上 我甚至懷疑他來不來接我

141
00:13:57,102 --> 00:13:57,659
Actually, I wonder

142
00:13:57,770 --> 00:13:59,635
if he'll even be here to meet me.

143
00:13:59,939 --> 00:14:01,338
WOMAN: There he is...

144
00:14:07,213 --> 00:14:08,805
WOMAN: Well, hop in.

145
00:14:11,890 --> 00:14:13,120
你好, 哈利
Hi, Harry.

146
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:15,882
你怎麼知道？
How'd you know?

147
00:14:16,027 --> 00:14:18,851
我是不會忘記外公的
I never forget a grandfather.

148
00:14:20,064 --> 00:14:21,456
你長大了
You've grown.

149
00:14:21,470 --> 00:14:25,257
已經過了16、17、18年了吧？
Well, it's been, what, six, 17, 18 years, hasn't it?

150
00:14:25,403 --> 00:14:27,054
我沒注意
I hadn't noticed.

151
00:14:27,110 --> 00:14:29,936
你沒收到我的留言 我想叫你別來

152
00:14:27,333 --> 00:14:28,300
Didn't get my message to you.

153
00:14:28,400 --> 00:14:30,163
I tried to head you off.

154
00:14:31,040 --> 00:14:32,661
你介意我來嗎？
You mind that I came?

155
00:14:32,938 --> 00:14:34,235
( bird squawking )

156
00:14:34,040 --> 00:14:36,171
算了, 你人都到了
Ah, what the hell. You're here.

157
00:14:40,050 --> 00:14:42,482
走吧, 我想在天黑前回到家

158
00:14:40,179 --> 00:14:40,668
Well, come on.

159
00:14:40,779 --> 00:14:42,713
I want to get home before dark.

160
00:14:42,654 --> 00:14:44,245
車燈壞了
Headlights don't work.

161
00:14:44,889 --> 00:14:46,242
你都沒變
You haven't changed.

162
00:14:48,130 --> 00:14:50,346
沒必要, 我也沒打算要
Haven't had to, and I don't plan to.

163
00:15:07,810 --> 00:15:09,407
好
All Right.

164
00:15:09,708 --> 00:15:10,606
( seagull cawing )

165
00:15:10,150 --> 00:15:11,220
好的

166
00:15:10,709 --> 00:15:11,733
All right.

167
00:15:11,649 --> 00:15:13,004
好
Okay.

168
00:15:12,851 --> 00:15:14,443
謝謝
Thanks a lot.

169
00:15:15,550 --> 00:15:19,319
號碼是在科羅拉多小鎮 烏雷的一家雜貨店

170
00:15:15,581 --> 00:15:16,707
The number's a general store

171
00:15:16,815 --> 00:15:19,375
in a little town in Colorado-- Ouray.

172
00:15:19,320 --> 00:15:20,918
哈利.傑克森沒有電話
Harry Jackson doesn't have a phone,

173
00:15:20,990 --> 00:15:23,390
但他們認識他 阿克斯特, 他們知道他住哪裡

174
00:15:21,086 --> 00:15:22,053
but they know him, Axminster.

175
00:15:22,154 --> 00:15:23,553
They know where he lives.

176
00:15:37,202 --> 00:15:38,669
( truck thudding )

177
00:15:41,974 --> 00:15:44,704
你是要摔死我 還是在嚇唬我
You trying to throw me or just scare me?

178
00:15:46,620 --> 00:15:48,473
你老是喜歡聊天
You always did like to talk.

179
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:19,200
還是那麼強壯, 對吧？
Still tough as a dirty boot, aren't you?

180
00:16:19,150 --> 00:16:20,744
一點都沒錯
You're damn right.

181
00:16:42,534 --> 00:16:44,297
( door squeaking and closing )

182
00:16:45,140 --> 00:16:46,235
怎麼樣
Well?

183
00:16:46,210 --> 00:16:48,430
又濃又熱的黑咖啡, 是嗎
Black, hot and strong, right?

184
00:16:49,050 --> 00:16:51,108
你都記得, 孩子
Nothin' wrong with your memory, bud.

185
00:16:51,420 --> 00:16:52,577
外婆說過
Grandma used to say

186
00:16:52,440 --> 00:16:56,954
除非咖啡濃到讓湯匙立著 否則你是不喝的

187
00:16:52,678 --> 00:16:53,770
you'd never drink a cup of coffee

188
00:16:53,879 --> 00:16:56,006
unless a spoon would stand up in it.

189
00:16:56,955 --> 00:17:00,253
你外婆從不放棄要我文雅些
Grandma never did give up trying to civilize me.

190
00:17:00,390 --> 00:17:04,156
那也許是她唯一做過的蠢事

191
00:17:00,552 --> 00:17:01,211
I guess maybe

192
00:17:01,320 --> 00:17:03,550
that was the only dumb mistake she ever did make.

193
00:17:05,160 --> 00:17:06,770
除了過世之外
Except maybe dyin'.

194
00:17:08,166 --> 00:17:10,029
所以你才離開我們嗎？
Is that why you left us?

195
00:17:12,170 --> 00:17:14,491
你總是一針見血
You always did get right to the point.

196
00:17:14,970 --> 00:17:16,462
你還是一樣
Haven't changed.

197
00:17:18,076 --> 00:17:19,500
是變得不多
Not much.

198
00:17:25,180 --> 00:17:26,334
要咖啡嗎？
Want coffee?

199
00:17:26,280 --> 00:17:27,503
好
Yeah.

200
00:17:28,550 --> 00:17:29,909
你還沒回答我
You didn't answer me.

201
00:17:30,090 --> 00:17:31,508
我離開…
I left...

202
00:17:33,530 --> 00:17:35,014
是因為時候到了
because it was time to leave.

203
00:17:34,850 --> 00:17:36,782
不, 爸死的時候你還在
No, when Dad died, you were there.

204
00:17:36,590 --> 00:17:38,413
你還在陪著我們
I mean, you were... you were there.

205
00:17:38,120 --> 00:17:39,959
我是待了一陣子
I stayed around

206
00:17:39,591 --> 00:17:40,148
for a while.

207
00:17:39,960 --> 00:17:42,500
老天, 我有權過我自己的日子

208
00:17:40,259 --> 00:17:41,351
God, for the love of Mike, boy,

