哈利

422
00:29:25,730 --> 00:29:30,724
你忘了教過我 怎麼誘捕動物了嗎？
Harry, don't you remember teaching me all about decoys?

423
00:29:31,729 --> 00:29:34,031
把這個裝滿樹枝如何？
Why don't you fill that up with branches?

424
00:29:34,160 --> 00:29:36,536
對, 弄個假人
Oh, yeah, and make it look like a man.

425
00:29:38,840 --> 00:29:42,368
我來看看能否 用這棵樹玩幾招
Now let's see if I can get this tree to do a few tricks.

426
00:29:48,680 --> 00:29:50,482
沒看到他們往這邊來
AXMINSTER: No sign of them coming this way.

427
00:29:50,548 --> 00:29:51,885
要繼續開嗎？
CARSON: Should I keep going?

428
00:29:51,916 --> 00:29:53,618
我們該搞懂馬蓋先
AXMINSTER: We should figure out MacGyver.

429
00:29:55,120 --> 00:29:56,590
再做決定
Then make a decision.

430
00:29:59,460 --> 00:30:00,960
艾法、柯林、貝克, 聽到嗎？
Alpha, Colin, Baker,

431
00:30:00,532 --> 00:30:01,464
do you read?

432
00:30:01,330 --> 00:30:03,430
這是阿克斯特, 看到目標了嗎

433
00:30:01,666 --> 00:30:02,462
This is Axminster.

434
00:30:02,567 --> 00:30:03,659
Are targets in sight?

435
00:30:04,090 --> 00:30:04,931
沒有
No, sir.

436
00:30:04,770 --> 00:30:05,329
沒關係

437
00:30:05,036 --> 00:30:07,129
反正是貓捉老鼠, 繼續走
No problem, it's just a little cat and mouse. Keep moving.

438
00:30:07,100 --> 00:30:09,297
你們聽到命令了, 通話結束
You got your orders. Over and out.

439
00:30:09,567 --> 00:30:11,036
好了嗎？
Okay?

440
00:30:11,369 --> 00:30:13,076
往高地去
Head up to high ground.

441
00:30:13,170 --> 00:30:15,275
對, 今天很適合打獵
AXMINSTER: Yeah, it's a nice day for hunting.

442
00:30:35,960 --> 00:30:36,998
哈利？
Hey, Harry?

443
00:30:37,030 --> 00:30:40,339
記得你以前告訴我 印第安人是怎麼作戰的嗎？

444
00:30:37,101 --> 00:30:38,159
Remember you used to tell me about

445
00:30:38,269 --> 00:30:40,533
how the Indians fought this way?

446
00:30:43,241 --> 00:30:44,401
孩子
Bud...

447
00:30:45,203 --> 00:30:47,539
我過去跟你說的很多事情

448
00:30:45,276 --> 00:30:46,106
a lot of that stuff

449
00:30:46,211 --> 00:30:49,977
I used to tell you is, uh, is stories.

450
00:30:48,410 --> 00:30:50,015
都是故事而已

451
00:30:50,310 --> 00:30:52,315
對, 不過很多都管用, 哈利
Yeah, well, a lot of it works, Harry.

452
00:31:02,493 --> 00:31:04,484
( Jeep approaching )

453
00:31:04,596 --> 00:31:10,626
( yelling )

454
00:31:14,930 --> 00:31:16,010
可惡
Damn.

455
00:31:16,700 --> 00:31:19,106
我還以為至少有車可以用了
Thought we'd at least get a free ride out of this.

456
00:31:19,037 --> 00:31:20,746
看來得繼續跑了
Guess we keep on running.

457
00:31:21,470 --> 00:31:23,411
那是阿克斯特, 快走
MacGYVER: That's Axminster. Let's get going.

458
00:31:36,890 --> 00:31:39,360
阿克斯特 另一輛車掉到山坑裡了
BLACK: Axminster, the other jeep, down in the gully.

459
00:31:46,400 --> 00:31:49,470
又兩個受傷 我們去把馬蓋先解決掉

460
00:31:46,571 --> 00:31:47,629
AXMINSTER: Two more down.

461
00:31:47,839 --> 00:31:49,534
Let's finish this MacGyver now.

462
00:31:56,240 --> 00:31:58,506
我頭昏眼花了, 孩子
You getting lightheaded, bud?

463
00:31:59,280 --> 00:32:00,544
松果？
Pinecones?

464
00:32:00,940 --> 00:32:02,417
沒錯, 哈利
Sure, Harry.

465
00:32:03,210 --> 00:32:05,414
試過丟一個到火裡…
Don't you remember ever throwing one in a fire?

466
00:32:05,450 --> 00:32:06,853
會怎麼樣嗎？
What happens?

467
00:32:07,385 --> 00:32:09,221
會炸開來
It kind of explodes.

468
00:32:09,421 --> 00:32:10,826
沒錯
Yeah, that's right.

469
00:32:11,320 --> 00:32:14,954
加點松脂, 就能做地雷了
Add a little pine pitch and you got the makings of a landmine.

470
00:32:17,595 --> 00:32:19,694
大自然很偉大吧
Ain't Mother Nature grand?

471
00:32:31,010 --> 00:32:34,240
你是要躲開他們 還是有什麼主意了？

472
00:32:31,149 --> 00:32:31,945
HARRY: You just trying to stay above them

473
00:32:32,050 --> 00:32:34,348
or you got some kind of an idea?

474
00:32:34,410 --> 00:32:35,714
兩者都有
A little of both.

475
00:32:36,580 --> 00:32:37,982
我可以的
No, I can manage!

476
00:32:47,320 --> 00:32:48,397
等一下, 哈利
Hold it, Harry.

477
00:32:51,160 --> 00:32:53,167
我想吉普車會從那裡…
I figure the Jeep'll come from there

478
00:32:53,565 --> 00:32:54,899
往這裡來
right through here.

479
00:32:58,040 --> 00:32:59,470
你在…
Well, what in the...?

480
00:32:59,840 --> 00:33:01,844
該埋地雷了
Time to bury the landmine.

481
00:33:05,910 --> 00:33:07,014
看到什麼了嗎？
HARRY: See something?

482
00:33:06,990 --> 00:33:09,187
沒有, 但我聽到聲音了
MacGYVER: Nope, but I hear something.

483
00:33:18,820 --> 00:33:19,899
該走了
HARRY: Ought to get a move on.

484
00:33:19,900 --> 00:33:21,900
時間多得是
Ah, there's plenty of time.

485
00:33:23,161 --> 00:33:24,666
你確定會成功？
You sure that'll work?

486
00:33:25,130 --> 00:33:26,131
不
Nope.

487
00:33:26,900 --> 00:33:28,666
孩子, 你還真會安慰人
Bud, you are a comfort.

488
00:33:30,370 --> 00:33:31,601
他們來了
HARRY: Here they come.

489
00:33:33,010 --> 00:33:34,544
快, 我們走
Come on, let's go.

490
00:33:44,220 --> 00:33:47,650
我小時候會把松脂當口香糖

491
00:33:44,389 --> 00:33:45,947
When I was a kid, I used to chew

492
00:33:46,057 --> 00:33:48,082
pine pitch like it was gum.

493
00:33:48,090 --> 00:33:49,590
味道還可以

494
00:33:48,326 --> 00:33:52,490
It tasted all right, but it burned a lot better.

495
00:33:49,955 --> 00:33:51,656
拿來燒更好

496
00:33:57,202 --> 00:33:57,802
好

497
00:33:57,468 --> 00:33:58,435
All right.

498
00:34:06,010 --> 00:34:07,568
( rapid gunfire )

499
00:34:15,253 --> 00:34:16,413
( grunting )

500
00:34:17,616 --> 00:34:19,115
哈利？
Harry?

501
00:34:19,751 --> 00:34:20,990
我沒事
I'm all right.

502
00:34:21,286 --> 00:34:22,653
丟過去
Get him!

503
00:34:25,563 --> 00:34:27,758
( yelling )

504
00:34:30,560 --> 00:34:32,396
來吧, 哈利, 我們快走
Come on, Harry, let's get moving.

505
00:34:33,700 --> 00:34:35,838
大家還好嗎？
AXMINSTER: Can anybody still move?

506
00:34:36,100 --> 00:34:38,835
夠好到能抓馬蓋先了
CARSON: Yeah, good enough to find MacGyver.

507
00:34:38,770 --> 00:34:40,535
看來我們也得走路了
BLACK: Looks like we're walking now, too.

508
00:34:43,980 --> 00:34:45,640
不是走, 是跑
AXMINSTER: Not walk, run.

509
00:34:45,443 --> 00:34:47,445
要他進黃泉
We'll run him right into the ground.

510
00:34:56,221 --> 00:34:57,759
不要緊的
Well, that's okay.

511
00:34:57,856 --> 00:34:59,426
只是小傷
I'm just dinged.

512
00:35:00,390 --> 00:35:02,088
我注意到了
Yeah, so I noticed.

513
00:35:03,230 --> 00:35:04,801
只是擦傷, 哈利
Just grazed you, Harry.

514
00:35:04,830 --> 00:35:06,230
有可能更糟
Could've been worse, you know.

515
00:35:06,804 --> 00:35:10,331
痛起來像很嚴重
Eh, hurts like worse.

516
00:35:10,669 --> 00:35:12,341
放在裡面
Put that inside.

517
00:35:12,200 --> 00:35:13,944
用力壓住
Put pressure on it.

518
00:35:14,673 --> 00:35:16,279
你還好嗎？
You all right?

519
00:35:32,891 --> 00:35:34,126
我們到了
We made it.

520
00:35:35,794 --> 00:35:37,161
對
Yeah.

521
00:35:37,800 --> 00:35:39,333
嘿…
HARRY: Hey!

522
00:35:40,970 --> 00:35:43,708
所以…這就是艾福莫
MacGYVER: So... this is Evermore.

523
00:35:44,342 --> 00:35:45,741
( coughs )

524
00:35:45,570 --> 00:35:46,771
哈利

525
00:35:45,877 --> 00:35:49,369
Harry, when was the last time you were here?

526
00:35:47,210 --> 00:35:48,910
你上次來這裡是什麼時候？

527
00:35:51,576 --> 00:35:52,910
太久了
Too long ago.

528
00:35:54,212 --> 00:35:55,484
是個死城了
It's dead.

529
00:35:56,414 --> 00:35:58,450
我猜我們也是
I guess we are, too.

530
00:36:00,890 --> 00:36:02,920
哈利…
Harry? Harry! Harry!

531
00:36:10,128 --> 00:36:12,226
該死的阿克斯特
Damn you, Axminster.

532
00:36:18,011 --> 00:36:22,543
所以我倆在這鬼城
So, there we were in a ghost town, Harry and me.

533
00:36:21,181 --> 00:36:22,315
哈利和我

534
00:36:23,150 --> 00:36:26,216
我盡可能讓他舒服些
I tried to make him as comfortable as possible.

535
00:36:30,260 --> 00:36:31,988
你在做什麼, 孩子？
What are you trying, bud?

536
00:36:32,158 --> 00:36:33,820
那是愚人金
That's fool's gold.

537
00:36:34,027 --> 00:36:35,495
有黃鐵礦

538
00:36:34,258 --> 00:36:34,815
Which contains

539
00:36:34,926 --> 00:36:37,656
pyrite-- iron sulfide.

540
00:36:35,895 --> 00:36:37,097
硫化鐵

541
00:36:37,831 --> 00:36:41,800
加點黏土混合起來 像是天然抗生素

542
00:36:37,929 --> 00:36:39,294
Mixing it up with a little clay here

543
00:36:39,397 --> 00:36:42,059
kind of makes a natural antibiotic.

544
00:36:42,102 --> 00:36:44,095
看看你的傷怎麼樣了
Let's see what you got here.

545
00:36:45,870 --> 00:36:48,934
你到底是做什麼的, 孩子？
Just what is it that you do, bud?

546
00:36:51,810 --> 00:36:54,706
一點這個, 一點那個
Well, a little of this, a little of that.

547
00:36:56,147 --> 00:36:57,876
( groans softly )

548
00:36:58,820 --> 00:37:01,190
那麼…

549
00:36:59,217 --> 00:37:04,814
Well, that... that sure explains it.

550
00:37:02,355 --> 00:37:04,391
那就難怪了

551
00:37:04,660 --> 00:37:07,049
你會沒事的, 哈利
You're going to be okay, Harry.

552
00:37:06,790 --> 00:37:09,894
有想過掛個招牌當巫醫嗎？

553
00:37:07,158 --> 00:37:08,284
Ever think of hanging out a shingle

554
00:37:08,392 --> 00:37:10,326
as a medicine man?

555
00:37:18,138 --> 00:37:19,736
我有話要說
I've got something to say.

556
00:37:21,140 --> 00:37:23,137
我一直在躲你
I've avoided you.

557
00:37:25,345 --> 00:37:26,976
知道為什麼嗎？
You know why?

558
00:37:29,049 --> 00:37:30,443
我媽
Mom.

559
00:37:33,253 --> 00:37:34,907
先是你外婆
First your grandmother.

560
00:37:36,756 --> 00:37:38,523
然後是你媽
Then your mom.

561
00:37:39,893 --> 00:37:42,115
當老天爺把她們帶走
When the good Lord took them,

562
00:37:42,929 --> 00:37:44,727
我很傷心
I hurt.

563
00:37:46,870 --> 00:37:49,400
我不願想起, 所以我…

564
00:37:47,031 --> 00:37:48,089
I didn't want to be reminded,

565
00:37:48,199 --> 00:37:54,138
so I just, uh, I just kept moving.

566
00:37:51,238 --> 00:37:52,939
我就離開了

567
00:37:56,310 --> 00:37:58,032
看到你…
Seeing you...

568
00:38:02,150 --> 00:38:03,610
我很想你, 孩子
I've missed you, bud.

569
00:38:06,219 --> 00:38:07,874
真可怕
Something terrible.

570
00:38:08,388 --> 00:38:10,243
哈利
( softly ): Harry...

571
00:38:12,390 --> 00:38:13,584
( sighing )

572
00:38:15,290 --> 00:38:19,157
這真是很可悲的一幕
Well, that... sure was a sorry sight.

573
00:38:19,263 --> 00:38:20,127
( sniffling )

574
00:38:20,166 --> 00:38:21,323
夠了
Hey.

575
00:38:22,170 --> 00:38:25,240
不准你說我外公壞話, 知道嗎

576
00:38:22,233 --> 00:38:22,790
Don't you

577
00:38:22,900 --> 00:38:25,460
ever badmouth my grandpa, you hear?

578
00:38:25,569 --> 00:38:26,194
( chuckling )

579
00:38:26,304 --> 00:38:27,862
( groaning )

580
00:38:30,076 --> 00:38:33,545
我要找些東西來跟他們對抗 你說呢？

581
00:38:30,207 --> 00:38:31,139
Look, I'm going to try and find some things

582
00:38:31,242 --> 00:38:32,300
for us to fight with.

583
00:38:32,410 --> 00:38:33,741
What do you say?

584
00:38:38,520 --> 00:38:40,850
你真的認為 他們會找到這裡？
You really think they're going to find us here?

585
00:38:42,050 --> 00:38:43,819
他們是職業殺手, 哈利
They're professionals, Harry.

586
00:38:44,257 --> 00:38:45,990
他們會找到我們的
They'll find us.

587
00:38:54,170 --> 00:38:55,970
哈利好好地休息了一晚

588
00:38:54,332 --> 00:38:58,098
Harry had a good night's rest, but I didn't sleep at all.

589
00:38:56,336 --> 00:38:57,671
但我完全沒睡

590
00:38:58,700 --> 00:39:02,210
我知道天一亮 阿克斯特就會開始追蹤我們

591
00:38:58,803 --> 00:39:00,236
I knew that, with first light,

592
00:39:00,338 --> 00:39:02,329
Axminster would be tracking us again.

593
00:39:03,343 --> 00:39:07,614
所以我得在那之前 做最好的防備
So, I had to build the best defense I could

594
00:39:06,510 --> 00:39:08,273
before they got to us.

595
00:39:13,620 --> 00:39:14,982
孩子
Hey, bud!

596
00:39:15,322 --> 00:39:16,886
你在做什麼呢？
Mind telling me what you're doing?

597
00:39:16,860 --> 00:39:18,784
我找到一些穀物屑
Yeah, found some grain dust.

598
00:39:19,192 --> 00:39:21,595
好好利用就可以做很好的炸彈

599
00:39:19,290 --> 00:39:19,915
Treat it right,

600
00:39:20,024 --> 00:39:22,254
we got the makings of a pretty good bomb,

601
00:39:22,130 --> 00:39:23,418
我確定
I'll betcha.

602
00:39:23,330 --> 00:39:24,629
效果可能不錯
Might work good.

603
00:39:24,630 --> 00:39:29,467
再弄點玄虛引他們來到 要爆炸的地方

604
00:39:24,762 --> 00:39:26,195
Got a little parlor trick

605
00:39:26,297 --> 00:39:28,322
to get them to come up close to where the explosion happens.

606
00:39:31,500 --> 00:39:35,370
有時榖倉裡的穀物屑會爆炸
Sometimes you hear about floating grain dust

607
00:39:33,771 --> 00:39:36,205
exploding inside a silo.

608
00:39:35,976 --> 00:39:38,639
那叫自燃
It's called spontaneous combustion.

609
00:39:39,513 --> 00:39:41,702
我則是刻意的
I'm going to do it on purpose.

610
00:39:42,050 --> 00:39:44,339
而我發現哈利真是個好搭檔
And I found a real handy partner in Harry.

611
00:39:45,020 --> 00:39:47,650
他想法就跟我一樣
He seemed to be talking just the way I was.

612
00:39:48,560 --> 00:39:51,519
或說我的想法一直像他一樣
Or maybe I'd been thinking like him all along.

613
00:39:51,420 --> 00:39:54,190
你的大爆炸只有一次機會, 孩子

614
00:39:51,655 --> 00:39:52,644
HARRY: Only get one shot

615
00:39:52,757 --> 00:39:54,190
with your exploding gadget, bud.

616
00:39:54,490 --> 00:39:56,182
你有什麼打算, 哈利？
MacCGYVER: What you got in mind, Harry?

617
00:39:56,230 --> 00:39:58,985
聲東擊西引他們過來
HARRY: A little remote control distraction.

618
00:39:59,170 --> 00:40:03,330
保證讓那些呆子來這裡 收到大驚喜

619
00:39:59,430 --> 00:40:00,590
Guaranteed to get them galoots

620
00:40:00,698 --> 00:40:03,724
to come up real close for the big surprise.

621
00:40:03,700 --> 00:40:06,826
孩子, 我從這裡可以像魔術師一樣
Hey, bud, I can play magician from over here!

622
00:40:06,470 --> 00:40:08,009
忽隱忽現

623
00:40:06,937 --> 00:40:09,132
Now you see it, now you don't-- and boom!

624
00:40:08,010 --> 00:40:08,840
然後爆炸

625
00:40:19,720 --> 00:40:21,341
好了, 這樣夠了
All right, that's enough.

626
00:40:21,250 --> 00:40:23,520
已經在搖了 我可不想它倒在我頭上

627
00:40:21,452 --> 00:40:22,009
It's shaking,

628
00:40:22,119 --> 00:40:23,643
and I don't want it falling on my head.

629
00:40:23,660 --> 00:40:25,930
訣竅是要讓那些呆瓜就定位

630
00:40:23,754 --> 00:40:24,846
Real trick's going to be

631
00:40:24,955 --> 00:40:26,388
getting those galoots in position.

632
00:40:26,330 --> 00:40:28,659
如果他們不站在正下方 就行不通了

633
00:40:26,490 --> 00:40:27,354
MacGYVER: If they aren't

634
00:40:27,458 --> 00:40:28,823
right underneath it, it won't work.

635
00:40:28,660 --> 00:40:29,722
你要去哪？
Where are you going?

636
00:40:29,590 --> 00:40:31,562
過來, 我也有一招

637
00:40:29,827 --> 00:40:30,555
HARRY: Come on.

638
00:40:30,661 --> 00:40:32,151
I got a trick of my own.

639
00:40:33,700 --> 00:40:35,889
這是什麼？松子？
What do you got, pine nuts?

640
00:40:35,769 --> 00:40:38,071
我小時候會拿來玩
HARRY: Yeah, I used to have fun with them

641
00:40:37,368 --> 00:40:38,995
when I was a kid.

642
00:40:38,305 --> 00:40:39,473
把它們丟到火裡

643
00:40:39,103 --> 00:40:39,933
I'd, uh, drop them in the fire,

644
00:40:39,770 --> 00:40:42,335
看大家跳來跳去, 松子會爆開
and watch everybody jump, and they'd crack,

645
00:40:42,270 --> 00:40:45,406
就像子彈一樣
and they'd go off like gunshots.

646
00:40:46,710 --> 00:40:48,550
他們一直被你騙倒

647
00:40:46,911 --> 00:40:47,639
Well, they've been falling

648
00:40:47,745 --> 00:40:48,541
for your foolishness.

649
00:40:48,615 --> 00:40:50,915
我想也來試試我自己的
I figured I'd try some of my own.

650
00:40:51,451 --> 00:40:54,516
我想哈利開始喜歡這遊戲了
I think Harry was beginning to enjoy the game.

651
00:40:54,850 --> 00:40:56,987
然而時間到了
And that's all the time we had.

